# Skiff whitepaper reference

Background context for secure email architecture discussions:

- **Skiff Whitepaper (2023):** https://skiff-org.github.io/whitepaper/Skiff_Whitepaper_2023.pdf

## When to reference

- Discussing key hierarchy design (account key wraps identity keys)
- Evaluating privacy/security trade-offs in mail features
- Comparing E2EE approaches with industry precedent

## Hierarchy of authority

This repo's docs take precedence over the whitepaper:

1. **[docs/e2ee-mail-spec.md](docs/e2ee-mail-spec.md)** — source of truth for ELVish mail
2. **[docs/adr/](docs/adr/)** — rationale for specific decisions (0003–0009 cover mail)
3. **Skiff whitepaper** — background context and terminology alignment only

When the whitepaper and repo docs conflict, follow the repo. Update ADRs when diverging intentionally from Skiff patterns.
